    <div class="s-prose js-post-body" itemprop="text">
<p>Few tips to help you solve your problem:</p>

<ul>
<li>you will need <a href="http://www.php.net/manual/en/function.uasort.php" rel="nofollow">uasort</a> function, to preserve associative keys</li>
<li>You can not access <code>occurrence_date</code> key directly from <code>$x</code> o r <code>$y</code>, you will need <code>$x-&gt;times[0]-&gt;occurence_date</code></li>
<li>Before doing comparison, iterate through <code>$x-&gt;times</code> just to check if there are more entries, pick one that suits your needs.</li>
<li>since <code>occurence_date</code> is a number you don't have to use string comparison function</li>
</ul>

<p>Good luck :)</p>
    </div>
